My advice is to take care of yourself. It seems obvious but itâ€™s easier said than done. 

One of the best things Iâ€™ve done is now reading before bed as compared to falling asleep to Discord/Twitter. 

The littlest changes can make a significant difference.

9/

Ultimately, like anything, it comes down to balance. Itâ€™s not easy to incorporate balance into a space that demands every second of your time. 

Many of us have others that depend on us. Many of us feel like if you step away for a few days youâ€™re going to miss something.

8/

I took about a week off and I feel exponentially better. I feel rejuvenated and excited to get back into the swing of things. 

The things that feel like they required all of my energy just a few weeks ago now feel much more simple. 

I feel like Iâ€™m back to a healthy place.

I empathize for people that have struggled with similar emotions and experiences. 

Artists that struggling with their creative process, builders that feel like they cannot do right, collectors that do not enjoy what they are collecting, etc. 

This isnâ€™t how we should feel.

5/

Everyone enters this space at different times. While I think overall things have got better since Iâ€™ve joined, I also think other areas have got much worse. 

As more people join, I get anxious at the idea of them picking up negative tendencies that are considered the norm.

4/

I found it difficult to respond to DMs from people I really care about in this space. I found it difficult to post tweets. Every little task felt like it required so much effort. 

As the days went on, I felt like I was letting more and more people down.

3/
